{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f64-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"40726"},"text":"§ 40726.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Allowances for junior competitors","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f65-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definition","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, a “junior competitor” is a competitor at the National Matches, a small-arms firing school, a competition in connection with the National Matches, or a special clinic under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t36/s40725"},"text":"section 40725 of this title","children":[],"tail":" who is—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f66-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" less than 18 years of age; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f67-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a member of a gun club organized for the students of a college or university.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f68-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Subsistence Allowance","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A junior competitor may be paid a subsistence allowance in an amount prescribed by the Secretary of the Army.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f69-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7","identifier":"/us/usc/t36/s40726/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Travel Allowance","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A junior competitor may be paid a travel allowance in an amount prescribed by the Secretary instead of travel expenses and subsistence while traveling. The travel allowance for the return trip may be paid in advance.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id747b1f6a-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/225"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–225","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-08-12"},"text":"Aug. 12, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/1338"},"text":"112 Stat. 1338","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id747b1f6b-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id747b1f6c-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"id747b1f6d-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source (Statutes at Large)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"40726(a) (words before cl. (1))","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:4313(a)(1) (words before “may be paid”).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"40726(a) (less words before cl. (1))","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:4313(b).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"40726(b)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:4313(a)(1) (words beginning “may be paid”).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"40726(c)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:4313(a)(2).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the provisions for a junior competitor to be paid a subsistence allowance and a travel allowance prescribed by “the Secretary of the Army” are retained notwithstanding section 1612(d) of The National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 1996 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106"},"text":"Public Law 104–106","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/517"},"text":"110 Stat. 517","children":[],"tail":") which transferred the Civilian Marksmanship Program, including the National Matches, from the Secretary of the Army to the corporation. The conforming amendments in section 1624 of the Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/522"},"text":"110 Stat. 522","children":[],"tail":") did not repeal the authority of the Secretary of the Army to prescribe National Matches under 10:4312 or to prescribe subsistence and travel allowances for competitors under 10:4313."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
